description: Returns a list of your queues in the current region. The response includes a maximum of 1,000 results. If you specify a value for the optional QueueNamePrefix parameter, only queues with a name that begins with the specified value are returned. The listQueues methods supports pagination. Set parameter MaxResults in the request to specify the maximum number of results to be returned in the response. If you do not set MaxResults, the response includes a maximum of 1,000 results. If you set MaxResults and there are additional results to display, the response includes a value for NextToken. Use NextToken as a parameter in your next request to listQueues to receive the next page of results.

parameters.name: QueueNamePrefix
parameters.description: A string to use for filtering the list results. Only those queues whose name begins with the specified string are returned. Queue URLs and names are case-sensitive.

nested_items.name: QueueUrls
nested_items.description: A list of queue URLs, up to 1,000 entries, or the value of MaxResults that you sent in the request.

nested_items.name: NextToken
nested_items.description: Pagination token to include in the next request. Token value is null if there are no additional results to request, or if you did not set MaxResults in the request.
